webpackJsonp([0xd220784f473],{1085:function(t,a){t.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<blockquote class="large">I\'ll be operating from the assumption that everything that happens in cyberspace is part of the same reality that our physical bodies occupy (sounds obvious, doesn\'t it?), and that a sustainable application of technology is one which increases our understanding of reality and moves us away from a passive consumption of virtuality to an active engagement with the Real.<span class="attribution">Ideant.typepad.com\n(Ulises Ali Mejias)</span></blockquote>\n<p>This is such a fantastic blog that I had to point it out.  His description of our role (as consumers) in a technological world (online) is just refreshing. I\'ve quoted a bit here from his <a href="http://ideant.typepad.com/ideant/2003/08/index.html">first month of posting</a>. I went back and found his first post, and I\'m trying to digest all three years of his writing. At least it is Sunday.</p>',frontmatter:{created_at:"January 07, 2007",path:"/2007/01/07/great-blog",title:"Great Blog",tags:["blog","reading","theory","engagement"]}}},pathContext:{}}}});
